.TH BOREDNOMORE3 1 "January 2025" "0.7.0" "BoredNoMore3 Manual"
.SH NAME
borednomore3 \- dynamic wallpaper changer with smooth transitions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B borednomore3
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B borednomore3
is a sophisticated wallpaper management daemon for Debian-based distributions.
It uses ImageMagick affine distortions to create smooth transitions between
wallpapers across all major desktop environments.
.PP
The tool supports 1000+ transition effects based on 7 core transformation
types (slides, rotations, zooms) and implements a true shuffle system where
no wallpaper or transition repeats until the entire collection has cycled.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information and exit
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-credits
Display credits and exit
.TP
.B \-D, \-\-debug
Enable detailed debug output with real-time logging
.TP
.BI \-\-config " FILE"
Use custom configuration file (default: /etc/borednomore3/borednomore3.conf)
.TP
.BI \-i " SECONDS" "\fR, \fB\-\-interval " SECONDS
Time between wallpaper changes in seconds (default: 300)
.TP
.BI \-d " PATH" "\fR, \fB\-\-directory " PATH
Directory containing wallpapers (default: /usr/share/borednomore3/wallpapers)
.TP
.BI \-f " NUMBER" "\fR, \fB\-\-frames " NUMBER
Number of transition frames, 5-100 (default: 10). Higher = smoother.
.TP
.BI \-s " SECONDS" "\fR, \fB\-\-speed " SECONDS
Delay between frames, 0.0001-1.0 seconds (default: 0.001)
.TP
.BI \-t " LIST" "\fR, \fB\-\-transitions " LIST
Comma-separated transition IDs or ranges (e.g., 1,5,10-20)
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-randomize
Randomize transition order (shuffle transitions, no repeats until full cycle)
.TP
.B \-w, \-\-randomize-wallpapers
Randomize wallpaper order (shuffle wallpapers, no repeats until full cycle)
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-keep-image
Keep previous image visible during transition
.TP
.BI \-l " FILE" "\fR, \fB\-\-wallpaper-list " FILE
Custom wallpaper pattern file (default: /etc/borednomore3/borednomore3.list)
.SH CONFIGURATION PRIORITY
Configuration is applied in this order (highest to lowest):
.IP 1. 3
Command-line arguments
.IP 2.
User config (~/.config/borednomore3/borednomore3.conf)
.IP 3.
System config (/etc/borednomore3/borednomore3.conf)
.IP 4.
Built-in defaults
.SH TRANSITION SYSTEM
The transition engine uses 7 core transformation types mapped to 1000 IDs:
.IP \(bu 2
slide-left/right/up/down (IDs: 0,7,14,21,...)
.IP \(bu 2
spin-clockwise/counter-clockwise (IDs: 4,11,18,...)
.IP \(bu 2
zoom-in-out (IDs: 6,13,20,...)
.PP
Each transition has two phases: exit (old image) and entry (new image).
.SH SHUFFLE SYSTEM
When randomization is enabled (-r or -w), the system creates a shuffled
playlist and plays through it completely before reshuffling. This ensures
true randomization with no repeats until the full cycle completes.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B borednomore3
Run with defaults (5-minute interval, sequential)
.TP
.B borednomore3 -D -i 60
Debug mode, change every 60 seconds
.TP
.B borednomore3 -t 1-10 -r -w
Use transitions 1-10, randomize both transitions and wallpapers
.TP
.B borednomore3 -d ~/Pictures -f 50 -s 0.01
Custom directory, smooth slow transitions
